                    "value": "offensive"
                },
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The forge-spurned breathes a cloud of stinging soot, ash, and glowing embers. This can affect either a @Template[type:cone|distance:30] or a @Template[type:burst|distance:20] centered on the forge-spurned and persists for [[/br 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>\n<p>Each creature that moves into or starts their turn in the area takes [[/r {6d6}[fire]]]{6d6 fire damage}, with a @Check[type:reflex|dc:21|basic:true] save. A creature that fails its save is also @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Blinded]{Blinded} for 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Creatures within the cloud are @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Concealed]{Concealed}, though not from the forge-spurned.</p>\n<p>The forge-spurned can't use Forge Breath again until it has used Inflate Bellows.</p>"
                },
